      title: "Dutch Customer Data API"
      version: "1.1"
      tagline: "Verify and standardize Dutch customer and business data — addresses, phone, email, VAT, IBAN, KvK and postal codes"
      homepage: "https://bedrijfsdata.nl"
      docs_url: "https://free.bedrijfsdata.nl/v1.1"
      license_short: "Free public endpoint, no authentication; license terms not published"
      license_md: `- Hosted as a free public endpoint at \`free.bedrijfsdata.nl/v1.1\` by [Bedrijfsdata.nl](https://bedrijfsdata.nl), an Amsterdam-based Dutch business-data provider.
- No authentication is required for the free tier.
- No explicit licence or terms of use are published alongside the free endpoint — treat the data as for development and validation use only, and check directly with the operator before commercial redistribution.
- CORS is not enabled, so calls must be made from a server-side context.`
      about_md: `This SDK wraps the free validation endpoint at \`https://free.bedrijfsdata.nl/v1.1\`, operated by [Bedrijfsdata.nl](https://bedrijfsdata.nl) — a Dutch B2B data company based in Amsterdam that maintains profiles on more than 3.7 million Dutch companies and organisations.

The free service is aimed at verifying and standardising Dutch customer and business records. Typical inputs and outputs cover:

- Dutch and international phone numbers (with country code)
- Postal addresses and Dutch postal codes
- Email addresses and website URLs
- VAT (BTW) numbers
- IBAN bank account numbers
- KvK (Chamber of Commerce) registration numbers

The endpoint requires no API key and is intended for lightweight validation use. Rate limits and a formal licence are not published; for higher-volume or commercial use, contact Bedrijfsdata.nl about their paid datasets and enrichment products.`
      entity_desc: {
        eu_ap_i: "EU-scoped validation helpers — checks for data formats that are common across the European Union, such as VAT (BTW) numbers and IBAN bank account numbers."
        global_ap_i: "Globally-scoped validation helpers — generic checks that are not country-specific, such as email address and URL validation."
        netherlands_ap_i: "Netherlands-specific validation helpers — Dutch phone numbers, postal codes, addresses and KvK (Chamber of Commerce) numbers, e.g. `GET /v1.1/phone`."
      }
      auth: false
    }
  }
